To support the provision of public services to meet the reasonable assistance needs of the people of Pitcairn (including health, education and securing sea access), given self-sufficiency is currently not a viable option for this UK Overseas Territory. This is in line with the 2012 Overseas Territories White Paper and consistent with relevant elements of UK’s Aid Strategy and DFID’s 2015-2020 Single Departmental Plan.

To address the needs of IDPs and host communities in the remote area of the Sudan-Chad border, through provision of emergency relief assistance (in the form of shelter and household items) where needed, but also includes early assistance for the re-establishment of livelihoods, water points and health facilities.

The DAC is a unique forum that brings together the world’s traditional donors in support of development effectiveness and sustainable development. Member’s voluntary contributions ensure the DAC can fulfil its role in holding donors accountable to their commitments and improving development practices.

To support a more democratic, prosperous and secure Egypt through technical assistance to the Egyptian Finance, Trade & Industry, and Social Solidarity Ministries provided by HMG experts; providing targeted support to female headed households in one of Egypt’s poorest regions; and delivering policy support to think tanks and grass roots organisations pushing for greater accountability and scrutiny of economic policies.
